Sentencas: The effects of introducing La2NiO4 nanocatalyst on the electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 are investigated under solid oxide electrolysis cell and fuel cell modes, as well as open circuit voltage.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: Extracted data from impedance spectroscopy are interpreted with the analysis of distribution of relaxation times.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: La2NiO4 infiltration effectively reduces the activation energy of the oxygen reactions from 1.35 to 0.99 eV.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: It also changes the rate controlling process of the overall reaction.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: Polarization behavior of La2NiO4-infiltrated La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 electrode shows superior performance under electrolysis mode compared to the fuel cell mode.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: Drastic increase in the size of low frequency arc during anodic current passage in the non-infiltrated La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 electrode is hampered by infiltration of La2NiO4 nanocatalyst.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: By applying anodic current on infiltrated La0.8Sr0.2MnO3, no displacement is observed in the position of high frequency peaks in the distribution of relaxation time graphs and only a small increase in height occurs for the low frequency arc.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4

Sentencas: Additionally, La2NiO4-infiltrated electrode impressively decreases overpotential by 74% compared to the non-infiltrated one under electrolysis mode at 800 degrees C.5
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 oxygen electrode promoted by Ruddlesden-Popper structured La2NiO4
